obo:ECO_0001225  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_1684  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Tubulins are generally important for axon outgrowth. In this paper a point mutation is made in TUBA1A-N102D, referred to as Tuba1a-ND. These animals show a lack of skeletal muscle innervation, which is caused by a defect in axon outgrowth (Fig3). On the diaphragms, the endplates of the axons that do make it to the muscle are disorganised and variable in size (average endplate area is 90±30 um2 in Tuba1aND/ND versus 70±5 um2 in Tuba1aND/+; Fig5 A-D). This is represented by de decrease in endplate potential amplitude and a larger asynchronous evoked response (Fig5E-H).. Experimental description: M&M:\"ENU mutagenesis was performed (Kasarskis et al., 1998) on males of C57BL/6J background and then outcrossed onto 129S1/Svlmj background to score generation 3\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-10" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1684" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

